\title{Discrete model of a simple double theory}
\taxon{definition}
\import{macros}

\p{Let \dbl{T} be a simple double theory.

The \define{discrete model functor}

##{
    \Disc: \cat{Fun}(\dbl{T}_{00}, \Set) \to \cat{Lax}(\dbl{T}, \Span)
}
is the left adjoint to the forgetful functor

##{
    \cat{Lax}(\dbl{T}, \Span) \xto{(-)_0}
    \cat{Fun}(\dbl{T}_0, \Set) \xto{\varepsilon_{\dbl{T_0}}^*}
    \cat{Fun}(\dbl{T}_{00}, \Set),
}

where #{\varepsilon_{\dbl{T_0}}: \dbl{T}_{00} \hookrightarrow \dbl{T}_0} is the
counit of the adjunction #{\Disc: \Set \rightleftarrows \cat{Cat}: \Ob}.}

\p{A \define{discrete model} of a simple double theory \dbl{T} is a model of
\dbl{T} in the image of the discrete model functor.}
